ascents.comment: pulled this one outta nowhere!
Try hard and wait for the shade!
keep it going till the end!
solo. really good line, maybe worth the hike?!
so quality!
went right, felt easy as tall man. should've flashed but punted top out
very good but such a tease with a drop off
flash
really hard in the sun, a lot better at night!
after fully rocking over right foot it felt like v4 for tall
a Pretty Okay problem!
tall boys dont cut feet until their hand latches the big hold. top out beta both feet up!

put in the time and work for this one!
edit: August 2019 downgrading to v6 because I have grown up to be a sandbagger
love it when crux is don't dab
always warmed up on this and one time i actually linked it!
quality, was tough to find that balance, and the jump is great!
one session, soft-ish but taking v6 because it was hot!
took a couple burns to figure out sequence, made me feel a lot better after a day getting shut down
great send train with CO crew!
turn around, be tall!
stared longingly/avoidantly at this thing forever as I projected morning dove white!
One of my favorite highballs. Naked Carsen
first v7! ~6 sessions. 2017-2018 proj
primo, must do! i didnt want to but I did! with the Washington crew
lots of anticipation, need to commit and such a good line! great way to close down the season
left crimp sticks better than it feels
solo, as the sun was setting. so many tries to latch the 2fing pocket, just keep hips into wall!
two sessions.. throw is a big commit!
few years ago first move felt impossible to keep feet on. get stronger and boom it goes! fun line
3 goes.. felt like a v5 for 6' 1"
tall man means i can swing my left foot up to the bat hang, keeping the right foot on the low foot!
sustained and reachy! crux is actually getting the right heel in the damn hold!
Day flash
Once I got my hips into a tall man position the big move was chill. Awesome tram slot. Had to fight for the top out
Trash problem
Waiting for the crew to finish pancake house. Felt so so.
Shouldve flashed but went wrong direction on top out
kind of silly and too height dependent
fun & a little sketch & herbert did it too!
not the least fun i've ever had!
2 days before 30th birthday, everyone sang me Happy Birthday as i topped out! 3 sessions: 1 to figure beta, 1 to punt, 1 to send
mega proj gave like 20 burns on first day, then did it first burn the next session cause im not actually that weak
One session
what a commitment, perhaps scariest thing i've done to date? 18 ft off the deck one legged squat with  jug foot but non existant hand holds
second session of the season, climbing horribly that night then all of a sudden poof I'm at the top. james owes me korean bbq
took a few years, but tall guy got to learn how to mantle!
i bitched about the high foot a couple years ago but now I realize tall helps on this one
hard for a six, probably best line of boulder
First send of the season and of a 23 point day
bleh, but I was there so might as well finish it
latching the jug was the best, as was the view of the moonrise over the sierras from the top
Felt soft but also i was tired so I still had to fight to finish it
one step closer to Vanishing Point! Took forever to finalize what beta I was willing to commit to
best v4 ever, second go
gave it a few sessions last year of failure, jumped it quickly this year. glad the holds didnt break on the top out

taking V8, got that integrity. first of that grade. 5 sessions, took 4 sessions for the v6 and did it quick next session. great movement & rock, and the 30 degree temps and snow on the ground didn't hurt
one of the most beautiful walls ever! send train!
New guidebook gives v5 which I think is fair. Second go while waiting (still waiting) for Sam to finish Sharma traverse
This bastard made my ego and skin angry for two long sessions, two years apart. I hate it. Second go on my next trip, was kinda fun
soft second go. no pads used = no dab. if this had a clean landing climbers would gang rape it
Cool movement at beginning but kind of ugly and sticking the toe hook is irritating. Soft maybe cause I'm tall.
ascents.zlaggableName: Jug Start to Acid Wash Right

ascents.comment: Tried literally 25 times a couple years prior with Carsen, this time went in a couple goes with Daisuke
Nadia and I day flashed after not jumping on this thing a bunch of times a few years ago. Hand and slab strength help!

3 sessions, one to pull my hamstring in 2017, one in 2018 to start hating it and say I'm not psyched anymore, and 1 to send when I used a toe instead of heel and it got cold enough that the sloper felt good (after I found where to hit it). Day 3 of 6 day new year's trip
Kinda fun, lesser done warm up. Unfortunate that it gets easy up top

Think this felt hard a couple years ago, went pretty easily this year. Took three short sessions cause of conditions, but did it on a perfect 40 degree windy day at the Happies with Johnny-Boy. Top a bit spicy, good fun
Soft maybe just cause the temps were good. First V5 flash? Never appealed to me but when there was pads and I was bored & solo I figured I'd go flash somemone's proj
Felt really hard last year, then hard this year. Warming up my fingers for Every Layer you Wear and did the big move first go using the high right foot, and put down the whole problem next burn
Miserable scrunched until Nadia showed me the foot she used, went down next go as I numbed out at the top. Super good. Nadia followed up shortly

Sub 40 temps at 10am on New Years Day after van got so cold our water froze overnight. Shade helped, made it feel soft for 7 but also it was fourth session. This marked successful accent of all climbs I wanted to do on our 6 day trip, how is that possible for a buffoon like me
standout in J Tree for sure, appreciate the jug at top. actual crimps and tensiony foot move or 2. felt V6 to me, surprised Bachar didn't sandbag more.
If this was anywhere else it would get at most 1 star, but for Jupes it gets 2 i suppose
Super good quality problem with positive moves and the right height and an even better name
Kinda fun, happy I could do a jump and hold the swing. Natural line is the 8 but the foot options are gross

misery incarnate. my left middle finger has never been so happy to be done. jumped to jug pocket. solo bolo day trip. rained the before, but no holds broken and all's well that ends well eh. scare tactics right will go down soon, unless the bouldy in the fall zone takes my ankle first

Second real session. Felt impossible over the years then poof I can do first move. Testament to core day. Punted lots of times, developed micro beta on keeping adequate grip on that shit sloper. Glad the holds at the top didn't break
This was fun. Got irritable on the precision needed for first couple moves. Amazing Grace still feels impossible
I'm tall I think it's cheating. I guess since I did this boulder that's like all the classics eh
Third go magic go, drop knee is cool, top doesn't flow so just jump through it. Descending into the valley felt like entering prehistoric dinosaur land. Cool.
Third go, soft, did it 3 times, crimps two thumbs up

Guide asys v6, Probably a v3. next to Contact. Should have flashed but misread the guide (with how excessively detailed the guide's beta is, how could i actually do this) and started on the wrong hold. then tried to top out wrong cause im blind. 3rd go
finally something not soft. burled. pumpered
my style, beginning moves went quick. punted on the top out twice until I took a hard fall on my A$$ and decided I was okay with topping out left.
No way this was V5. First introduction to the true softness of New Joe's. I give it v2
Guide gives v6, Felt like v4. Not very good. Streaks of sap on the holds is clutch
First legit v5 flash? Dabbed on a cut but still taking it, fight me. My style. Streaked up the hill, is cooler but not my style, so can't tick that one
Dale. 3rd go. Burly
Never felt so tenuous and bad on holds and still actually topped out. Slab king. Sharp shit
This boulder was so rad. Cool movement and as someone said, like Pork Chop and Atari had a devil child. My style went quick
Another legit 5 flash. Felt easy. Epic downclimb bro
Super cool movement and rock. Soft for a 7 I think no matter what height? Handful of goes. Ignored everyone and did a right heel hook mantle, and epic win. Played some Dead while working it

Handful of attempts. Went quick after I figured out right hand to first big pocket then cross left to second pocket. Screw underclings eh. Rained out after figuring my beta and did it first go today, after much anticipation anxiety. It's so good

Vegas buffet on the way home = earned. Ugly but double knee bar cool. Did top out in iso but couldn't do it during problem, so took a video and boom turns out hips don't lie, did it next go. Thank God for beta spray from Jackson 5 on this one
Guide gives v6, Another v4-ish soft thing. Joe's grades kinda irritating. Fine rock climb.
Guide says v6, More like v4/5. Warm up with the Washington kids/families

Sit doesn't go;from the stand. Strong finish to amazing trip. Such cool holds, but could go for fewer teeth on the pocket. Once a Spaniard told me to use high foot with the left, it went quick. 2 sessions
More like v3? Has this on the to do list for some reason. Move to lip was cool with tension

Jug hold w/ undercling, second hold of v2, was on. Can't see it going without it. Fueled by 6th strip of bacon from the red rock buffet brunch, plus perhaps the kale salad and biscuits (are just a spoon you can eat) and gravy

This bad girl has taunted me for years and it went down casually first climb of the season. What a first trip of the year.. This flowed, then flexor strain on Staph when it was about to go down in one session. Couchchella
couldnt do it 2 years ago, a warm up for me now. victory.
V8 in one session? No.. it's soft. Cold today so took the opportunity to peel off up to the 'bergs. Sit feels gross
It was cold and cloudy so thought I'd put my newfound finger strength to the test and they passed. 3 sessions over the span of years
First problem in a 32 point day crush-a-thon. First go of second session, last crimp is so sharp that there's only a few real try hard goes. cool underclings glad we trekked to this.
eh, interesting movement. took me a couple years but not too hard at my current strength once i paid attention to my feet
v6 next to green peace. Cool problem, revenge sending for it injuring Nadia. I couldnt make moves on it last year and it went down in a few goes this year
Almost retro flash but slipped a foot once or twice. Unique one. Who looks at this and thinks to climb it. Trained it
ascents.zlaggableName: Standing On The Head Of The Dragon

ascents.comment: Awesome boulder, committing moves and good movement. One session last year and did in a few goes this year including a pumped out punt from the top
Worth doing as a warm up but thats it. Jump down from top was fun for all. Beginning of a tromping-through-the-snow day

Rained out of Black, made a switch and 3 hours later we are in windy wonderland of Josh. This frustrated me earlier in the season... there's no I in send, needed some Roland counterpoint beta and it went down!
Surprised more people aren't down grading this. Felt v5 at most, maaaaybe harder if you are like 5'4" or shorter. Fine enough problem, send with herb and Roland, don't want to hike here again

Could barely pull off the ground a couple years ago, did it quick with ease this time. Training works and improvement happens!.. even if I don't believe it. This feels like a problem that stronger climbers cant imagine giving harder than v5, but v5 climbers struggle with
Cool techy movement. Soft perhaps, and good fun. Sucked it up and bought another annual pass
Wow that was fun. Not even scary! I think when I first did the v2 a few years ago I said I'd never do Illuminatrix.. look at me now ma. All tee'd up on Barefoot Sharma
Finally made it up, cool one on the hottest day. Wanted the flash but I tried to be too tall. Bailed right to jugs for top out
Not as turdy as it looked, but kinda a turd. Slopers were good baking in the July sun
Flashed after doing Malcolm. It was fine. The holds are there so might as well traverse I guess
Very good, send train with the cliffs boys. Smash Bros prepped us
This was very cool. Jaunt away from dance floor. Maybe felt easier than humping walrus, even in the beating sun
10 stars! Really fun gym style into a committing top out. Had to figure my own tall man top out mantle
This fun especially with a 6 foot pile of snow 1 foot away from the boulders. Paul did a v10 so I did a v5 and then he couldn't do the v5
psyched on this and went I think 3rd go. What a great first day, exceeded my expectations

wowow so good. Pulled the stand outta my ass when just sussing out the moves, then did proper sit second go after that. Height helps for keeping the low left foot, but then hips did work lifting that left foot disgustingly high
second go after committing to right heel. Pads got ultra soaked from water runoff, worth it? Double dyno is hard.
so hyped after G23 and Jedi Jake that I did this in 10 minutes
first mosquito infestation of the trip. Insanity. Gotta flash to get outta there. "feels like a gym v3" -Herbert. And I say reach for a peach feels v12
So good. Deserves ultra classic. As per Eli, always second go everything
Low start, yooo bat hang beta, wanted the flash too bad, hard head paid off till I noticed the bat hang.
mosquito infestation gives the necessary motivation for my first v6 flash without any warmup. Also it's ultra soft

about 45 minutes. So hyped when I saw it, and so underwhelmed when I topped it, not sure why. Felt soft and movement wasn't that cool, though in retrospect maybe it was cool. Maybe I'm too tall so I skipped good stuff.
amazing experience in the dark under the stars. Second go from start; emitted an involuntary grunt. This one felt good. Powered by fresh van baked white bread

9th day on and this was exiting consolation prize after no send on Lost but not forgotten and Scoop. So close on both but no skin, no strength, and little remaining psyche means we be bailing to Kings Canyon
Doesn't feel like a real rock climb. Like I'm sussing the top out of the sit.
4 sessions LOL. Soft when it went. This climb taught me that the heel size on shoes does indeed matter. Topped out right on jugs, you do you
Tried this years ago. Seems hard for shorties. Jump to the lip & cut was good fun. So hot I was overheating
Went left to knob from low crimps. Going straight/right up is heinous. Fun. Redemption since 3 years ago this was terrifying
Fell off the pad while trying to mantle on my flash burn. Maybe felt hard for 5. Third go. Worth doing while up there. Also, Undone Greg Loh Proj is sick.
A person's first of the grade (v9) is likely worthy of a downgrade. Probably v8. 2 sessions. Fit me perfectly. Wasn't even cold and a gash in my sweaty finger so I'm taking 9
Cool line little, would be quite nice if foot holds crumbled less. Laying back is fun when it's easy
4 sessions? Worst hold on the mountain. Did the move 3rd go then couldn't do it for 40 more goes, donated a hole in my finger and then eventually it went when it was too crowded and greasy waaa :((
as far as traverses go I guess this one is passable
One interesting move (out of a grand total of 3)
fine climb that felt so easy for me and hard for everyone else. a disappointment on the adjacent and much cooler (but so hot outside) Zack's Roof
Am I the only one who's done this who actually knew this was a band (and liked them) before sending? Felt impossible last year. People say it was hard.
Redemption after getting rained out earlier in the year. Worth doing but only barely. Guess it's popular for the same reason I did it: by the car, and short. Still, I learned something from it
Probably a 3 or 4. Felt easier than the Chief down the hill. Maybe I'll do the Chief one day (when it's not baking hot)
Sent everyone's project. Not that cool. 5/6 I guess. Taking six points for the 666 day
Looked better than it climbed. A warm up none the less
Three of us did, three very different betas. Rock quality a little lacking but movement is cool. Three stars in the book is generous, as was the v7 grade
swinging for the fences on this one. getting to where the only projects at tram are ones that just frustrate me
About 30 minutes. Feel sorry for anyone who tries this without the wingspan. Beginning sequence was cool, top was choss
Went in one session, thanks to Amazing Temps and great support. Felt soft once I dialed it in. Did not expect to send and this capped off best day of bouldering with v6, v6, v7, v8
Taking v6 because I started right hand on the higher right. Couldn't pull off the ground with proper start. Poor rock but good movement and primo mantle
Don't hear this talked about often but it was superb. Fun tension moves on good holds to a technical but not scary mantel. 27 points today excluding warm-ups
Fun solo one. Soft for my 6'1 body, should/could have flashed
Cool moves, would be quite cool if it was taller
Scrambled over to this to steal beta. Fit me perfectly I think and felt like v6ish

Maybe soft, maybe body position. Went out at night to support after a full Happies day and it went down in about 10 goes.
An image of dedication I won't soon forget: a hungry James at Pizza Factory watching his friends eat dinner so he can stay light while he waits for me to pick him up to go to the Milks.
Toe hook made it feel soft or maybe I'm tall. Second go this session, sessioned it once a couple weak years ago
Pretty awesome. Nice to think back to a few years ago when this looked silly impossible
Still can't flash v6. Quite the grovel fest. Reminds me of Greasefire at Tram
No heel toe cam for me, I'm not that creative. Took 20 goes or so, one session. Grazed the pad on the send go as I cut on the big move. Didn't help me at all but I'll asterisk this send
Very. Quality. Felt like v3/4
All my recommends. Temps help. Been on my list for a minute

Unique experience of both numbing out and greasing off, thanks to cold and humid. Doubted myself on every move. Soft for me I think because I can reach the high left sidepull while still keeping left start foot. Sent this rig after it drew blood
Pretty cool movement especially the double heel start. Silly top out but welcome to the ice caves. Grats Nads on Strength in Hooties!
Great movement and boulder
ascents.zlaggableName: Whiskey, Beer, and Splif hits for breakfast

ascents.comment: Soft now that I did it. But, it's not. Glad it's done
1st go. movement on this boulder is fun. snowy day means climb the drop offs. Ho took everything out of me and no send.
Very good and isn't as painful as it sounds, but still lots of pain. Find aaaaall the hidden holds up there! Second session
Wowow so good. Retro second go. Snow on the normal downclimb meant I got to down climb the v0 I've been meaning to up climb

Five gastons in a row, even though I didnt have to use the sidepull things that shorter climbers use I think I was still trying v8 hard and gastons with good feet are just my jam. Dropped off, I was by myself
Movement turned out to be rather cool once someone tipped me off to ignore underclings and cross right back to R crimp, high L foot, L to undercling then L to left crimp, then lock off to jug
Good route and great boulder. First v6 flash. Hike to Twilight is real.. and v10 is hard, but doable?
First day of the rest of our lives. Bailed on the uphill snow to the milks and put down this guy that's been on my list.
M flash and one of the last ascents before Big Jon broke the left hand start hold
Train with Rebongalong. Pretty cool.
Never felt like I was slipping off so many holds for so long. And then foot holds crumble off as I'm trying to top
Finish absolutely would not go in the sun. Went down first try when I had patience for later in the day
Good route! Not as scary as I thought
Nice movement, big holds, nothing too sharp.. Good way to kill time!
Been on my list forever and glad I flashed it. A bit soft for my tall height and therefore maybe underwhelming, but I guess it moved exactly like I expected
Eh. Bicycle was cool. Few goes, shoulda coulda flashed
ascents.zlaggableName: Work is a four letter word

ascents.comment: "Superb"! Starting from the lower shitty right crimp certainly adds difficulty but not necessarily quality. But I guess it means I know how to drop knee. Does that mean I can Get Carter now?
Felt hard but fingers were tired after flailing on Finder's Fee. For a tall guy this was a lot of perching on shitty feet. Movement was good
Six or so attempts. I think I'm better at compression climbing. Local said "you set that heel better than anyone I've ever seen"
Lived up to the hype. Latching was so good. Just need some hype boys with some pads
Almost gave myself a flexor strain on this guy. Left is grosser, this is gross. With Danny boy
My soul wants to take v7 but I'll just call it hard v6. Really cool tension and power. With conditions and the thumb catch, the last right hand is reasonable
mflash. So good.
Scarier and harder than Arch Drude
L gaston on the right crimp, jump right hand to jug. This was actually fun now that I did it that way
Very good one, and the reason I was psyched to hike back up to the Druids. On the way up I was thinking "I forgot how hard this hike was" and now that I'm down I already forget again
Can't take a v6 flash for this. V4 if you aren't short
Stoked this felt easy after looking at it in awe on my first trip to the Happys years ago
New favorite moderate at the Happys. Highly recommended
One off the life list!
Right hand straight up to finger jug, did not use the gross right slopey pinch/crimp. My style on that lock off, inverted rows ftw
Good movement and a fun one the Rim. Three windy sessions. Super close to finishing Paper Crane same day for the triple 8's
Pretty mega. Harder than King Tut
Really unique and cool one. Loving them lowballs right now. 3 sessions. So finicky
Finally actually did the proper v5 instead of the right variation
Almost like this better than Serengeti. Fun train with the west LA crew. Our last weekend in Bishop!

I was so irritable that I couldn't remember my sequence that the wife was ready to divorce. But I got the send and kept the wife. Sharp but cool movement. Hit it at 9am to avoid the sun. Not many v7s in the milks
Happy to top out Drifter for the last climb of our 25 day Bishop trip. Off to Death Valley. Third go because that rock over is really something
Tunnel boulders have a couple appealing lines on lackluster rock. Lots of great water landings. This lowball choss pile we did
Good enough line with fall zone rock

social distanced trip not a soul in sight. tired of this virus shit and its related anxiety. so nice to be out in the trees. in last 45 days all ive done are a few weak-ass hangboarding sessions. couldnt do God is Dead but i think that was more cause so hot.
Aka soy sauce memorial arete problem. Getting some fitness and skin back in the game. Corral is so sick
Good fun one. Guess my quarantine crimp strength is bad because I did this v6 way faster than the pride, I couldn't even start Updog v3/4
so terrified at the top of this one.. my head was not in the game. wanted to bail towards the top but too high to jump and too sweaty to downclimb so only way was up
Another day, another v4
My mega quarantine project, that this took 3 sessions shows the lard ive become. Nice to put down

Shout out to the bat in the hold who let me shove my hand and feet in his face over and over and only squawked a few times. Temps today meant I had to make the hike from closed gate. 45 minutes isn't bad for a soft v8
Nice lil warm up. Black Mtn is sharp. Vulgarine feels doable, a year to the day since I was there last
Nice techy crimping and floating up a face. Marion Mountain has got me flipping psyched
Learning how to top out. And so close on Lohbo
First touch of that slick Yosemite granite. The King was also slick hence my punts on the top out
kinda trashy. but its nice to top out a boulder

Superb line on a beautiful boulder. Also superbly soft. V5/V6 or probably a v4 moon board problem. Couldnt commit to the top out on the first session in June heat, came back next night and FiReD tHe RiG first go
psyched on this nemesis that frustrated me hard last year. Tuolumne is magical

v8 feels pretty on par for me because my height made the middle moves pretty awkward. 3 sessions last year, one session this year with the send at high noon on a 76 degree day. Foot cut on last move and dabbed pad after I had fully latched jug, I'm convinced it didn't help but still, no one likes a dab. Shout-out to Jon's second cinnamon roll. EDIT: i think my beta was bad
Actually pretty fun for a long traverse. Pretty classic and feels like something the trad climbers of old would have warmed up on. Got rained out after this send

Logging this mainly because I want to note the memory of working Solar Power Sit in the dark, deciding to walk back to the van to grab a different shoe, then completely lost and unable to find the boulder for 55 minutes
Fun shit. Turns out dyno-ing isn't actually hard, you just have to do it.
Beautiful and great. Felt pretty secure up there, first move was probably physical crux. WTF is going on with the v6 sit though, cant find holds that make sense
Collecting them stars. Is that 20 stars for the day?
Good climb in between spittings of rain. 3rd go this year
One of my favorite lines in the Meadows so far. Perfect.
not really 2 grades harder than the stand, probably because the stand is closer to v6. Turns out holds feel better at night. But the holds on Mean Green still haven't felt good
soft 4th go doesn't have the same ring to it. Really really good boulder. returning for the sit
good good line. Almost felt casual once I could lock in heel toe cam. Love beta videos. But still, pumped out doing the sit to either of these lines. Gotta return
One move dyno next to Hit or Miss. Fun move, but maybe more like v5/v6. A one mover thats actually worth doing if nearby
Great warm up wall

3rd go. honestly felt probably v6 to me. I think even shorter people can keep the toe hook for the big move, so it doesn't seem like my height helped all that much. fun line but confused about the grade
few goes. Figured out I had to jump.. Then jumped.  Fun little problem. Jumping can be fun, even off small, sharp, painful crimps.
blew flash cause of sun in my eyes. Very nice and pure line. Closer to v5 really
5 goes or so. Really nice, pure line. Guess my fingers can do a bit of work now. The sloping rock its on takes away from the aesthetic for me, is it just me?
wow what a top out. Fun traverse besides that
quite a good line, not sure why it only gets one star but it's good face climb fun. Soft for sure
fun line in one session last year, one session this year. Amazing how finicky it is to switch the heel to a toe
First go after doing Charlie Don't Surf
Reachy as hell. Dirty as hell continent flake
First go after sussing a couple moves. How bout that sandy washboard road on the way up tho?! Can't pimp those Apocalypse Now underclings, can't deal with Mad Max, this felt quite a bit easier
First go after sussing individual moves. Really good, my height made top less committing. Sooo close on Serpentine but didn't latch last hold. Boulder is sharp, it drew blood from three index fingers
Sharp but good movement. no warm up, can't tell if my tendons or skin hurt worse. The v4 section is nice face crimping
ascents.zlaggableName: It's Not Easy Being Green Sit

ascents.comment: Great wall. Big day with crew, two sends on Jedi Jake sit and two on Jedi monkey. No rest days. Is C85 too sharp, or what
Not so bad really. Kinda dirty, kinda sharp. Started left hand on arete, then didnt use arete until basically the topout. Perched on a slopey left foot that blew and took some of that shin-skin
Once I figured out the first move, it was the crux on the v6 section that was the hardest. So its Soft. Still, 3 sessions. Loved getting lost

i agree with "Andy the Eagle God" - sit move doesnt necessarily bump this two grades, but its a very good move. this problem felt so much worse on a 75 degree day than the stand felt on a 55 degree day
Adds more fun movement to this beautiful boulder. Love it. Glad I never have to down climb again
Superb line. Always wanted to do it, but intimidated. Afternoon thunderstorm brought in Temps, and this went down 2nd go. Soft. Not that tall really, just comitting
These crimps were real nice. Cool line. Gave myself stigmata flapper on throw to horn. Also we FA'd the new eliminate line, avoiding the first R hand crimp. Tensiony gastons
New school classic three stars? Generous. But still cool. Flashed Chris' proj in a hail storm
2 sessions. jug is on, right? matching on that funky pockety hold was so awkward. this boulder makes for beautiful photos. not ugly at all!

Somehow got myself in an awkward position for the top out, really sweaty and screamed "i think I gotta bail!" then looked down and realized I really didnt want to take that fall, somehow topped it out. Props to the person who ticked something on the topout that totally isnt a hold
1 session! the start moves seem heinous - glad I'm tall enough to bump to theLeft hand finger stack from the start Right hand undercling. really fun movement besides that finger stack hold
From R crimp and L jug, cross R to flake, match as L gaston, then lock off R to lip
V8 in the guidebook felt more like v6. Would have flashed but didn't look at top out. Drop knee start. Enjoyable first few moves
Heel toe cam. Blargh
"Unnamed Low V6" #12 in guidebook, next to Buttermilk Simulator.
really cool movement to a slopey topout. maybe would have flashed if I hadn't had a shitty tape job on my sweaty finger
Good few moves in a shitty little alcove. Coltrane (v6) is fucking hard?!
One move dyno to a dirty ledge. This boulder.. could be skipped
Good movement and commitment, this boulder seems to be lacking on the rock quality on top
Fine line, some volume on volume day. Nice rock on the first few holds. Seemed soft
I didn't use toe hooks. Per Charlie Barrett start hold is jug, and rock below is on for feet. Cool moves
Love the tension and commitment needed on this one. One of my favorites in Tuolumne
Went quick. Didnt see a knee bar. Just some core engagement
Basically a flash but I dont want this to be my first v7 flash. I pulled on once to figure out where I wanted my foot to fit the knee bar. Cool moves, very unique for Tuolumne
Less dabby than it looked at first. Fun for a campus boulder
Reachy little guy to start with. Fun compression/balance moves to a bit of a committing topout. Recommended when its not blazing hot
No knee pad. I'm so bad at knee bars that I had to look up a video to see where it would be placed. Super obvious. Soft
Really enjoyed this and it put my core to the test. I didnt use/want any knee bars, just a heel/toe cam to get into the v7 start. Super unique for Tuolumne and really happy with this one. 2 sessions

4 sessions, took about 40 goes to stick the 1st move, then realized I was scared for the top out. Rehearsed the top and when I finally stuck the move a second time, took it to the top. Cherry on top of 57 days in Yosemite. As soon as I finished this, I was ready to leave everything and move to greener pastures

Soft? Last climb of this trip. Drove the hour from Lee vining just so I could knock it out before heading to Yellowstone. Chris finishing the softie 7. Nice boulder nice place. Till next time eastern Sierras!
Went quick after I got the tip to jump to the block. Cool line, start is so unique but didn't add any difficulty for me. With the SLO crew
Wow can't tell if things are glassy because of sweat, rock quality, or conditions. First climb done in CO!
Few goes, got spooked up at the top by myself with two pads.
Starts left hand on sharp sidepull/crimp, right hand on slopey bad hold. Make big move up to juggy holds in seam, then up arete
Felt hard but I'm also sweaty. Gave 'er a grunt. Cool line

Great movement. Solid v8 feels right. Did it in the drizzle so it can't be much harder than that. Took some time to figure a doable sequence at the bottom. Crux for me was the big L hand move from the match to the sidepully slot jug
First day at Mt Evans, an alpine paradise. Flashed this cause I'm tall. Bierstadt and Dali are hard but I'm psyched
more rain. used a literal puddle jug for the top out on this. progress on Dali, nadia tweaked her back, maybe some progress on bierstadt toe hook beta sequence
Beautiful easy slab
fine little warmup. I'm realizing there are some damn sharp holds here

6 sessions and 36 miles of hiking over 9 days. a long and winding road filled with rainy sessions. felt like v8 when I did it, v10 is still warranted. love Mt Evans scenery and rock but geez that hike
3 sessions, movement using the high R pinch is far superior, but still a little awkward
Amazing climb starting in a hole and ending in a top out into heaven
Kinda thrutchy tricky move to fun climbing
This would be superb if there wasn't a rock at your back. Still quite cool. Did this within an hour of arriving to Chaos for our first time!
Feels like lots of hidden holds. Once again unfortunately dabby, would be a solid boulder if it was alone in a meadow
More like v4/5. Shut down so hard today on Storm shadow and Whispers of wisdom
Cool movement. No knee bar. 65 today, 18 and 12in of snow tomorrow. Stuck the first move on Whispers!
this was fun!

About 30 minutes. Soft in good conditions. Early snow storm meant we got that low elevation climbing in Boulder. Quite a good boulder, rock is funky here. Also sent A-7 while it was dripping wet, the 7-year long lip traverse proj
kinda turdy that you traverse over to a ledge that you actually seems like a natural start of a real problem. or you can mantle way too early instead of traversing.

Really good boulder. I dont know what grades are anymore. I think everything is soft, if I can do it. Then there are things that feel impossible like Deep Puddle Dynamics. Great first day out after the snow storm
movement was more fun that I anticipated. so hot at 2pm, quite nice at 6pm. Bush pilot is inspiring; I am lazy
kept L hand on sidepull crimp, feet were on starting hand holds, bumped R hand to sloper lip. Manageable but not heinous. Someone said this was "way harder" than Freaks and Geeks
Should have flashed but I thought that left hand gaston was sharper than it was. It was sharp, but manageable
Probably deserves more than 1 star!
The sloper felt absolutely terrible, had maybe my worst skin day ever. Cool moves! Glad to tick off the classic. All that talus hopping tho... and wish there were more v5-v8s in Chaos

Its my style and felt hard for an 8. Did it in about 30 minutes though. Exactly 1 hour from Bear Lake to Meadow boulder, as fast I as I could. Totally draining. Shoutout to all the stashed pads I found keeping me safe. Also shoutout the most epic bail on the mantle of Skipper D and then too tired to get back their again. Do I care enough about finishing the climb to hike again?
ascents.zlaggableName: Far Left El Jorge / The Core

ascents.comment: Great line, my first session I bailed on the mantle cause of fucking sweat, then couldnt finish it off. In a rage and hiked down the pads cause screw hiking up again. Two days later we are back up here and it goes first go of the day. Shoutout to the 5 stashed pads I found, I'm safe!
beautiful rock, kind of a shit match or a heinous cross. as audrey said, the big fingered man was the one who matched & sent!

v6 if you're tall and can keep the left heel for multiple moves, v7 if not. techy mantle when you dont notice there's a jug in your face. got pretty OVER climbing in the park the last week, gave some half assed attempts on Real Large and Tommy's Other Arete, now we be bailing to UT! Also shoutout free access to Moonboard at Estes Park Mountain Sharp giving me justification to not climb outside
Fun little guy. Route 5 v8 felt hard. Really impressed with the size of this canyon, rock quality not sure about. Nice stop on the way to Utah
Movement was pretty good. But my God the sand
First day in Joe's and already got a techy mantle under my belt!
thanks TucsonDad for the top out beta.
recommend. Unique moves. So hard on first day in Joe's, felt smooth first go today. Is this what they call a day flash
this was cool! Nice big moves top a fun topout. Went ham and tried every line on this boulder tonight. Can't climb harder than v6. EDIT until the next day when I did the v8
holds & feet are too good for 6 points. top of my list since I first saw it online. Really fun face climbing. Work all day at the food ranch parking lot, send all afternoon/night
taking v5 like everyone should

Took a nice knee banger when my foot blew on the top out. Went and got the brand new solutions, and it went down. Thanks Bishop Mike for all the beta. Would not have thought of that foot position for move to jug!
taking v6 like everyone else probably should
Improper dyno. Good climb. Scouting out hard climbs today, Battletoads is gnar, playmate is possible, death scream is.. who knows
ascents.sectorName: Cabin Fever / The Perimeter / The Death Scream Area

ascents.comment: Pretty fun up to a glory topout, aside from the sharpness of the left hand crimp. Grande move
Saved on the topout beta by my top out guru Mike. Good route, v6 feels about right. now Team Effort on the other hand...
V7 if you're tall. Maybe v7 if you're short too if there's someone with more creative beta brain. Really cool moves. Somehow a lowball and a highball.
Quite a cool feature. To start on underclings, definitely used the gigantic slab boulder for feet, even though its detached. Thanks for Mike beta
More like v5, good moves! Mike says learn proprioception and onsighting boulders will take a v8 climber to v10+!
Superb line, adventure time at the Flu, love Joe's. Skin so wrecked omfg
Really good line on river near 8 mile. Surprised this took so long to be found and done!
at least it wasnt as sharp as No Substance
GOOD. Shortly after I sliced a big split for a second time through a second finger in three days while cooking
hard I think but also the glassy rock quality on the 2020 version of this climb is a bummer. Angler took me like 7 tries to repeat
didnt feel sandbagged with the Mike beta. Up the hill with joey. 3rd time this week ive said "this is the sharpest hold i've ever grabbed"
few goes. this boulder provides so many routes!
really good. but in what world is this, or the route next to it, v4??
about v5 probably.
Good moves on this one. Thought the last blind move was annoying, but once set up in a good position, it was nice.
Pretty fun really. V6 about right
Fun one with the Aaron and crew
Good warmup on a cold day. Fun moves and tricky top. V5 consensus from our group
quality line, frigid to cross the river. Aaron says harder than the flu!
good for a two mover lowball

Starting: there is a right hand sidepull crimp. I did not start here. Started right on edge on blocky pinch, left on wide sidepull/undercling. First move was left hand to lip. Diversion while ryan, tina, andrew crew were at Wills
Good, just enough commitment. until the flake up top breaks, then it will be a bummer. Phil with the punts on Heatwole
V5 is where it stands. Good ol Monday night after work sesh. Maybe next year, Eden (note to self hit Eden L hand crimp high on the gaston so there's room for all fingers)
Pretty soft, committing at the top but not hard. Dope feature. Followed Andrew to the top and a nocturnal mouse greeted me as I topped out
7th day on? OMG my right hand fingers are so wrecked now. When you're really having to bear down on that good Chips crimp bucket, thats when you know its time for a rest day
soft. good boulder. stacked with them 10 ft classics
flashed it but yeah cant do pocket rocket lol
Sketchy dirty topout indeed. Foot hold broke on the mantle, scary. This happened to be the lip hold for Reduced Fat Milk, whoops
Quick send revenge for Maddy & Andrew. Helps a bit to be tall I think. Dopppe. Almost as hard as Black dahlia jk

Tried to start matched underclinging arete holds. Hell no. Start L hand arete R on super low tiny shitty crimp. Move R to juggy sidepull and hold the cut. Good line, fun topout. The standard new school start of L arete and R juggy crimp sidepull is v5ish
Psyched to top this out, last of 31 days in Joe's. didn't send anything harder than v7, baffling, but love it here none-the-less. in the 30s all next week so we be bailing southwards
great way to warm up after fixing a propane regulator and leak in the van
Beautiful rock, went quick after Andrew pointed out we should position our body to grab the hold the way it wants to be grabbed. Top out didnt feel bad. OMG last climb sent at Joe's
Hey cool. Topping off the first day of our stint in Moe's

pumpy until i nailed exactly how to grab holds/feet, and ticked them. I'm better at climbing ticks than rocks. guess I'm in good company (J. Lucas) with this being a boulder that capped off a 666 day. Couldnt keep the heel on Indolence, couldnt sack up on Gription. Dry fired 3 times today wtf. bad skin or humid? or bad boy.
Quick send first boulder of this year, when I couldnt/wouldnt send last boulder of last year. Liked this one quite a bit
Really attractive cave with good lowball moves to an easy topout. Good warm up to punt on Indolence and overuse my right hand, then punt on Gription
Paradise found! This was cool enough that I didn't mind how close to the ground it was. Grunted it out. Recommended, unique steep crimping for Moe’s

Recommend. Might be v7. First move wasn't too hard for me but high left foot and using those tiny left hand crimps while I was constantly greasing off every hold made it hard. Unique for Moe's and full value, a bit scary.
3 sessions, and dry fired and backflopped off the stupid slimpers every session. Finicky fucking heel.
Made quick work of it in the dark. Thought I couldnt jump but maybe I can just a little bit. Started matched on the undercling cause that seemed right
3 sessions, had to figure out how to grab the slippery right hand. jump toe hook move is dope. this send broke my hard problem dry spell.
probably v6 but I guess I should give it v7. i'm a real boulderer.. got pumped out over and over on Underwhelmed which is 100% jugs, but did this short problem quick
So good!
Moe's balls hang low

About v7 Started matched on flat undercling way down there. First two moves felt like crux. Def harder than starting left hand in gaston hueco like a lot of people do. Really cool one, sandstone makes for the raddest features
Good shit! Stressful work, tenants, but still sending boulders tonight with a nads who's overstoked on Indolence
100th v6! Could have flashed if i 1) committed more to jump, 2) sussed how to grab lip holds.

I did the jug exit from the jug rail. Guess thats v6 but it didnt feel soft. I think 1) I feel pooped right now and 2) first time climbing roof pockets. Couldn't hold the cut on Dinosaur Direct, too scrunched on Power Up
I eat choss like you for breakfast
Hey It's Cool Guy
Stoked to do this on the second day of our stint in Red Rock. Out here with og factory crew and this didn't feel ultra soft but I also have no endurance
M flash, full circle climbing experience, in awe ~6 years ago seeing this climbed, first this morning popped on my shoes and ran laps. The West LA crew stronk today
Dug this one, even though it split my tip and then kept climbing and split it deeper. Dabbed once hard on the send go, did it again and dabbed 3 times. Taking it. not v8 though
Trained today by factory Asian mask delegation. Psyched. Soft
Used the jugs towards the end of the roof cause why wouldn't you. Felt soft if ya got the core. Ultraviolet though... Mmm
Odd line.. if you use the jug, you must dab. If you avoid the jug, its hard. progress on Ode
V3 from the good left hand right facing flake
Frigid warm up for Ode.. it's.happening!
Cold in the canyon beat us down. Beautiful wash. Cumbersome to get to boulders. Good rock climb
Good fun line on good rock. Knee tweak on Ode yesterday meant the approach here was... oof
V5 at most with the arete. Direct eliminate is cool but I ain't got that high foot power. Body falling apart. Outdoor psyche minimal at best. Life hard, but life good
Really dope line. A bit reachy. Love the canyon rock. Clogging the feed next
Pulled on a couple times and tried with the tiny feet. Realized you could use high right heel, or just campus. Get to da Choppa is so much harder
Felt soft but I'm a sand bagger. 3 star line. Send crew with Roland nad & audrey
Some pretty cool movement. Didn't use a toehook, just grunted through the match. The girls took some Gnarly falls jumping to the jug!
Didn't use the sharpness on the left hand crimp, instead grabbed the top of it and used thumb catch. Quick solo send after the crew left. 2.5 sessions. Feels good to do something semi-hard
First move felt pretty hard for me, but rest is okay. But i'm tall + can't undercling. Peruvian flake still gold. Cold day
Prob v4. Hope detroit isn't as dumpy as this boulder problem. Spitting venom is sharp, ultraviolet is awesome and hard, I am soft
Today I said "am I just over rock climbing?"

Felt hard for v6 I think.. still some pretty cool movement and features. Perhaps my most pathetic topout ever, but at least I didn't bail. Fitting name for me, a guy trying to cut Christmas weight before the Hueco trip
Maybe my favorite line on the wall.. the big throw was pretty cool, and traversy movement into it was dope

Went pretty quick in the blazing January sun. All the front lever progression training seems to be coming in handy for these Priest Draw climbs. On the other hand, tendons on both my wring fingers are sore because my fingies cannot handle them pockets
Felt soft I think but unclear on the line. This is an impressive roof/wall!
taking v4 this thing felt harder than the v5s. awesome, but irritating, pocket poxed roof
Shoulda flashed, shoulda visualized. Solidly good line. So much rock in the world
First problem in Hueco after anxiously browsing all day. Should have flashed
Almost flashed. Felt soft for the tall among us. This climb made sense to me.. most other stuff at our first Hueco walk-through looked intimidating!
First time using a knee pad and happy with myself that I figured out the beta and sent within about 30 minutes. Good thing I wasn't in a Planet Fitness cause I grunted on this one
beautiful. felt really stout for v3. Did all the moves on Theater of the Absurd on first session?
Tried to escape the wind, ended up in a wind tunnel
Tried hard and got pumped even though the boulder is only like 4 moves. Steven's left foot on the dimple was key for first couple moves
Dope
Pretty rad, reachy mantle but good climbing
Movement at Hueco is insane.. got a sharp steep crimp line right next to the roof sloper insanity of Choir Boys..
Few goes. Sharp but good
Saw beta with knee bars, but I'm too tall so just do a couple drop knees. Turns out 2 days on, rest day 2 hour planet fitness workout does not make for rested me. Nadia hates Hueco climbs
still learning how to toe hook.. had to stand up while catching the toe hook to exert upward pressure. after this, shut down on V7, V8, V9, and V10 today
Four sessions. Hard for me. T-Rex compression, soapy holds, and real finicky right heel. Flashed the v9 sit moves but four sessions for the v7
Can't in good conscience take any more than 6 points for this. Rad. Getting stoked again
Good steep compression. Work and send, work and send
Enjoyable compression but three stars in the guidebook feels generous. Soft despite the heinous crimp. Maybe harder if you're shorter. Bring lights. Stoked I did this in a session without beta
Definitely taped my index fingers. Hot out there
Trex compression for first sit start move. Felt v4 and real fun from there. The crew is here but we had a snowstorm and then got rained out of Lobster Claw. good ol' Texas hospitality
sharp. first good weather day with the west LA crew. daily ding dong dose felt harder. wanted to see sharp run but i be cold
Really unique, I can die happy knowing I climbed the weirdest rock in the world
This one was really solid enjoyable compression climbing.
drop offs are the best. Great movement. Tall slopey mossy top outs baffle me. Feels good to be psyched.
damn, a lot of climbing of 220 grit sand paper. Nadia and I both exclaimed about the pain!
holy shit 5 stars. first climb at Rocktown and I love it
Love these crimps and moves. Perfect texture on the rock
Amazing rock here, the quality and the features/angles. Very cool movement, went down once the sun went behind a cloud
radical. Should have flashed but needed slight beta tweaks. All time
Love this iron rock. Or is it stromatolites??
"i hate jumpin ughhh" and then immediately sticks the jump next go. good quality. these rocks though
needed youtube to teach me how to mantle
started matched double gaston in the pod. went into the traverse top out. felt v5. the direct Papparazzi felt lame
That's a good one. Our first day in New England and what a crag this is. World class v5. But so much wetness
Nice little but hot damn the v10s here are radical.  Pipe Dreams is doable and Speed of life is beautiful
Cool spot, not a strong day, good rock! Gotta just jump guys

Felt pretty casual once I had all the movement down. P-Way has some quality. Now that Im logging it I realize that the left or right start is contrived, cause really why wouldn't you just start on the crimp rail right in the middle bouldering lol
Work skin and finger strength ever, still pulled it outta somewhere. Cool climb, granite like Black Mountain
v6 at most. soooo sharp jesus christ this place. cool consolation prize after Satan's Sister Sally reminded me I ain't got the finger strength I want. Bryan killed it tho
v6 if you're tall. felt just as hard as Spragueasorus
Good one, sharp but everything is sharp about now. We've got a window of ~4 days of good weather so we are hunkering down in Rumney
Simple problem that's made good by the tensiony left hand move to the lip.
Really good. Some sharpness, but great movement. Took some skin, and then I hang boarded!
Pleasant rock climb. I guess it looks like "the gunks" in Tuolumne.. kinda! And just found out we are planning are Tuolumne/Mammoth trip this summer, getting psyched
Either I ate too much pastrami the past week in New York, or v5 is really hard here
Did this from the juggy holds, not the slopey crimps, and it was superbness. starting on slopey crimps is not for a man of my size
Good bloc, productive day out trying to get reacquainted with not being a turd
Cool line. What dab? Everything after this felt hard. Beautiful view from the ledge, but all mountains east of the mississippi are really just hills
Rad jump. Power through mods quick
flashed, v5 if we are generous, but we aren't, its v4
Amazing setting and love the size and angle of the wall. Holding the cut was harder than I thought, but still probably v6
Cool sequence in a verdant gnat field. Thought I destroyed myself yesterday but had enough juice for more stars
Today we are glad for drop offs because it rained the last 2 days straight and it's water world here. God damn the 10s on freds cave feel stout, I'm soft
Cool warm up, what a fucking wall this is! So much driving to get here
thanks for the fucked up directions Mountain Project. Otherwise, really sweet line. Surprised myself with some progress on Ab Lounge, beautiful line
last climb which took the last of everything out of me and I had nothing left for Off the Rails
Cool holds. Don't know about world class v4, but still 3 stars as in a very good v4 for a crag. props to Nadi for perseverance and finishing it
tall enough to keep my heel for almost all the moves. felt v4 that way. nadia fighting through the hand, elbow, hip, knee pain to get close
Cool line, Nadia shows me how to flash. Couldnt/Wouldnt do the sit.
last climbing stop on our way back to sunny southern CA. with Chris and this felt a bit soft but also greasiest pile
Enjoyable first send, with Chris, at our new home crag
V6 seems fair. Social party with good condis today at Black

Started compressed, not matched on the left arete. I dunno! That's how we were told to start. Then we read the book says to start matched,but that felt hard,so we said that started one move in compressed was the "natural start"
Cool mantle that I definitely wouldn't have figured out on my own
Softer for tall, my style a bit cause it went quick, but also it's hot and the season is over it seems. Good weekend with desh and mok
This is the only line worth doing in Water Tower
Compressed the arete and topped out on left side of the arete. Felt v3/4. This area blows 8)
I don't know where this starts, if it's on the two slot crimps, or if it's Right hand on the closer crimp and then left on a shitty pinch/crimp next to it. I did the latter
Awesome movement and one of my favorite mantels. It's been 3 years since I came here and it went quick today. 90 degrees in idyllwild was perfect for slopers
Enjoyed some movement. Sharp and so hot.
good one, took some time to figure out beta and that mantle is silly
baking night session with the crew at the home crag. grateful for rock climbing. sweaty
Felt hard for tall, ow my core. So psyched to up in the verdent green with the epic views. Shut down on karate kid, need fingers + biceps
Good one out a long day with crew. Bad skin and don't feel strong but we should still love life
Unnamed V6 on North side of Pywiack. Hot week trip with lots of obscurities. Psyched on the hard shit and good time. Bad skin
Obscurities tour on the last day with the crew
warm up obscurity tour, first time to tram in 21 months and boy its a lovely place
One of the best at the Flats. Rolled my ankle on barn door arete. Oww
King line, first hard send at Black of the season, even with an ankle sprain 2 weeks ago. Perfect chilly breeze here, blazing hot 8th dimension, and cold and damp @ Born under punches, what a day
fun jump
we all agreed, two stars was generous
Not the best rock quality but a nice little view and movement sequence
After a few sessions on that slippery sidepull, I got tipped off to the beta and it went.. Huge R hand to sidepull, then L hand heel on flake all the way to gaston pinch

Prob v7 but I've gotten old and soft so why downgrade. One we found the correct heel toe cam place, went down immediately. Two days of antihydral in the preceding week made the tooth manageable. Good day before the Halloween party
Exited left, cause we dont climb eliminates. V6 at most. Cool roof moves but unsatisfying top out. Still, unique rock for black
Quick direct variation. Took some power but probably v6. Gets dark earlier that I thought.. The Tilt Shift journey in the dark was something
That's a good one. Not much else of excitement between this and Stand and Deliver but boy howdy that's a nice one too, bushwacked and I can't do it
This line was cool but nothing harder on this boulder made sense. We hiked up enough canyons for one trip, next day was 80 degree kraft

the last move is the most satisfaction. too in my head to do the start moves (blaming on fatherhood in 2 months), happy to take v7 for it and this was a long coming send. Tye took it down next sesh after a full on ground fall from the last move. ran into lots of people + celebrity crew and enjoyed Solitaire (so close, progress!) and Xav's Roof
now that's how you start off the morning. loved it, finally. not much for me in Milks main so headed to dale's.
Probably could've have flashed in front of the alaskan guy. fun few moves, I guess pockets arent the worst thing in the world
real quick, probably soft if you're tall. toe hooks were bomber and that's a good sequence.
Broke the beta! Good times back here and felt soft for 8 but probably not v7. 2nd go from the start somehow.

not hard but I'm tall and can just reach the juggy arete hold while still in the bomber drop knee. like 5 sessions cause I always get almost to the topout and feel greasy and save it for "another day." decided to just finish it and remember how to top out tour (L up to top of boulder before reaching around right), followed quickly by the boys doing the namesake line
3rd go or so. Psyched on the density in this area. Hard if you don't have span but still felt soft. The 1st day of Christmas and my true love gave to me two v8s in our advent calendar

Echo all of Shirley's comment.. Not hard but still took me 3 session. Flashed all the individual moves and could do the last move in iso on repeat, but fucked it up from the start. Powered by Mayor Max's sucralose, corn syrup, and corn meal. Still not doing Expat. I guess it isn't v7 so soft v8 it is
doing new boulders is fun
AKA "Angry Marmot." turns out even the sharp turd covered in a tree isn't an FA, it was already in the book. we'll get em next time austin
woulda been a v6 flash but we needed janitor austin to clean the holds and show me mantling is easy. I'm not a picky man, all i need is a one star climb and thats enough for me
satisfying mantle amongst the project shopping in Parallax

more like v7 prob. josh has some quality rock actually, I had forgotten! nadia out with her big belly, might be the last time before they are family of three trips. close on Pumpkin Monzonite but whats up with my skin, and also Palm-O-Granite, maybe scared more than skin though
for Vera! awesome line still felt hard with perfect conditions.

"not exactly an inspiring line" we elitists say. But cool moves. Tops out with holds on the right side of the arete? Vera did well today, thanks girls! Can do all the moves on Forms, yeah I am indeed stronger than mid lockdown
quick send on a great trip to Tram that reminds me how damn good the rock is up there. popped Right hand to crimp, didnt touch bad middle sloper
Just working the crux of Left Hand of Darkness and turns out I did this problem, totally forgot about that. Strength is stronger at the moment!

From May 2020 covid proj to doing it quick the day gate opened this year. I'm better and stronger. Love my fam and Nad's daily sacrifices. Top isn't that bad if you just flip Ya right hand. Took me till the send go to notice that. Sunset yelps of joy
hard to grade single move boulder but that cut felt hard for my height. terrible skin, lots of trudging, thanks to Mike for the tour
Cool one on a fun day. Last move felt ez, it's a moon board v5. Three inches of progress on Left hand
Wowow. Rock up in the high zones is superb. Rad flash and psyched on the low. And psyched on all of it
Cool movement for 10 seconds and then you get to enjoy that "quality tram rock" -Eli sills. Vera having lots of fun with Nads on the blanket while I sent
Biffed flash, SSGNSN (Soft Second Go No Suss Needed). Slipping and sliding and I guess I might be kinda back in shape after two fat European months

This climb is drastically different if you start in a stand start undercling/jam vs. sit starting down pull. Book doesn't dictate it clearly. The latter felt impossible with long legs, but turns out starting double undercling and just reach straight to blind crimp wasn't all that bad when I realize I should stand up into the holds.
Chris is the ranger that is supposed to check Black Mountain Rd each spring and re-open the gate, and Andy is his boss. Shoutout to Lee the Chimney Sweep
Matched on the left arete as required. Wasn't actually that funky it turns out. Still fun movement. Learned how to mantle on 8th Dimension today
Snuck in a quick one on nadias climbing day
Cool shit after the MS meet up. Hey I can pull off the ground on Anthem, just barely
Soft for tall Boi. Still takes me a minute to mantle. Couldnt get past second move on any of the 4 cool lines in the zone, but damn they cook
Surprisingly fun once I figured out how to avoid death crimping that tooth. A confidence booster
Focus on that heel James said. Smear left push foot Perry said. Team work makes the sends work. Send train and James with the tour sit caboose. V6ish movement into one hard move.
Feet first goes! First hike of the season up the road. Peaceful with snow, no people, and lots of lil animal tracks
retro flash real good boulder, there's actually holds on it, so its probably v3/v4, saturday's for the boys, etc
That's a good one. Great day out with the fam with perfect weather and company, and Culp is cool!
Not v8 but a fun throw to a jerg. In the sun
retro flash felt chill cold from the ground. Start of a good time trip with crew
kinda spooky at the top
v5 at most with a knee pad. And that's only cause grandstaff stand felt maybe stout. Also yes, we used a knee pad on this

bump R hand for second move, obvi. In and out of that rain that day, couldn't go to Ode with the crew but this silly thing worked too. Cant believe I didnt see the topout hold when I almost finished it in the dark on my first session
thanks for the snow kraft boulders

Okay some people start right hand on the slopey pocket near the arete, some start on the deep two finger pocket which is wider and lower. I did the latter cause it's the hold I saw. Maybe it's v9 if you start on the slopey one but my hold was lower so duck off and gimme 8 big ones. 40 degree wind whooft
Unique for j tree and has cleaned up well. I thought it was soft but then the crew couldn't do it so maybe I'm a strong sand bagger. Made the crew wait an hour :(

He's back baby. First post-partum v9. Few session in 2020, hot sesh in 2022, then send relatively quickly today. Perfect conditions personally (good sleep, good diet, good poops) and environmentally (62 at the strip, perfect in the shady canyon). Brings back confidence I needed. 5 goes today, all better than the last. I think I'm stronger than ever! Maybe soft if your tall for 2nd/3rd moves to get established on undercling? Also, topout way better when I cross matched the jug pocket, kept Left in the jug, went Right big to the crimp on the slab
Came to it cold and did it in about 30 minutes. Maybe v7 with toe hook for left reachy move? Feeling fit

First go after figuring out tall guy beta. Went from "oh no a toe hook boulder" to send in 15 minutes. Looking forward to the extensions. Love the canyons. Bailed off the top of Astronomy twice whoops

Whoa thats good with awesome hop. Bear down that left crimp. Felt like I had to crimp hard but also did it in 30 minutes so cant be that hard. Triassic is good and comfy at 39 degrees and sunny
Better than Great White? This was the only new climb I did in 7 days in Joe's. close on Resident Evil and stoked on Eden. freezing and/or snowy most days. Bryan & Scott crew.
Silly climb, beautiful day, climbs are still going. Bachelor weekend with the big crew
Didnt feel hard today, tempted to call it soft, but tall helps on this one. Putting down everything at Tram that I want to
receives a coveted upgrade. First move limit. the kevin and herbert of 2017 would be so proud of us today

Well heck yeah. Soft if you're taller? The jump for the jug slot seems physically easier than the left toe on the slippery edge but it took me like 5 sessions to stick it because jump was so low percentage from the start. This is the king line of Tram for me (plus Somewhere in Time), and I stood atop the king. First go of the day and I had to convince myself to do the trek to Tram a couple times because c'mon I should know, the only way you send is actually getting out there!
Last cold day of season. Credit goes to father's day Carmel corn, hiking back to the car cause I forgot the fan battery, liquid chalk, and temps. Home door to door in 3.5 hours.
Rompin in forest on the last leg of Aug in France. 88 and humid everyday we are here. This was easy but also I have no endurance but let's get mileage. Nice sector
Second day in font, hot with Vera and the full crew, a lot of blobs in this sector that weren't so inspiring, but Action Directe was cool and maybe a couple others
That's a nice one. A little crumbling choss on the face crimps but otherwise real good. Hype volume skin thinning day
Technical mantle, why are some boulders so featured and others are blank
Good send with Dev, started left xeno right on bad pinch on arete below xeno. Double pad stack. If it didnt require pad stack and the holds were less dirty it would get 4 stars
Reachy, good tech mantle and its a real pointer finger crimp test piece
felt v3 but I'm tall. Good memories trying this with K Riley and failing, then doing it quick by myself years later. How far I've come

okay I started this with Left hand on the normal crimp and Right hand on a micro-shard directly next to it, and high right foot on nice good foot. Still hard this way. But I guess book says start R hand on that lower hold, so you start with a low right smear-ish toe and you gotta just yeet to the rail? I'd rather just call it v7
Not the worst line, enjoyable traversing. What a stellar boulder but oof those holds on Hopscotch are just slopey enough

V4/v5, took four of us two hours to figure it out. Dug a hole in my good shoes sitting on the good crystal starting foot over and over. Reachy, couldn't figure out reasonable shorty beta, and 12 o'clock boys felt nails
Better than El brute. Grainy but good movement. Conditions getting good. Body is wrecked from Tour Sit

V3 if you're tall
Felt hard to me, getting the right foot up was a process. This was the only climb I fell on today. Daisuke said v2

Book says start two chest high crimps. We think Right one broke. Pioneered started matching left crimp. Everybody (including me) starts high left hand but that seems to skip first move. Good climb. Probably v6 from high start. First go after it had been on my anxiety list for a few years. Good day at the groupie sites with the big krew
Beaut boulder in Cole's Food Court zone. Low start is gnarly. Dab factor is real but oh well. A real blowass on the mountain today
Daisuke found the clutch super low left foot for the start move. Starting right hand took big gash out of my hand. Good boulder but dang. I know this felt impossible last time I tried it

Lots of moves are easier if you're tall. Tried to send in snow storms last year and it went quick first trip this year. Had to maximize that heel toe cam. Bailed on all my friends at Red Springs to come to Kraft the holy land. But missed Christmas tree lighting with the fam. Love red rock
High start, real easy after Austin led the way two years ago.. Bucket full of water
Grabbed a micro and.. Didn't jump cause yeah OK.

11 sessions this year,few last year. Generally forward progress everytime, plus a couple rainy days. Thank God I sent the first time I made it to the stand. No epic. Arrived at 12pm as the sun blasted, decided to ask wife to be patient at home in the throes of potty training, swept snow from the top, then did a couple guys at groupsites. Returned at 3pm, 48F & 48% humidity,somehow fired first go. Brave gorilla at the top and mostly psyched to be done. 161.5 and Christmas burger celebration
Shoulda coulda flashed. Probably the only thing I'll send on this trip cause all I wanna do is project
Real good full value line. Traverse looks cool until the top out
Would be good if it wasn't bad. A v3 at black mountain

Probably flashable, almost exploded my knee with silly topout beta. Proj was baking in the sun so I waltzed over the way over here

Great day romping around and sampling the wondrous movement climbing provides.. this squeezer, resonator crimper, roadside slab footworker
